title: Alphabet Inc. Cl A stock rises Wednesday, still underperforms market
text:
Shares of Alphabet Inc. Cl A 
        GOOGL,
        +0.04%
       inched 0.55% higher to $145.94 Wednesday, on what proved to be an all-around positive trading session for the stock market, with the S&P 500 Index 
        SPX,
        +0.11%
       rising 0.96% to 5,000.62 and the Dow Jones Industrial Average 
        DJIA,
        +0.12%
       rising 0.40% to 38,424.27. The stock's rise snapped a two-day losing streak. Alphabet Inc. Cl A closed $7.84 short of its 52-week high ($153.78), which the company reached on January 29th. The stock underperformed when compared to some of its competitors Wednesday, as Microsoft Corp. 
        MSFT,
        -0.17%
       rose 0.97% to $409.49, Amazon.com Inc. 
        AMZN,
        +0.31%
       rose 1.39% to $170.98, and Meta Platforms Inc. 
        META,
        -1.68%
       rose 2.86% to $473.28. Trading volume (21.4 M) remained 8.5 million below its 50-day average volume of 29.9 M.
